1.   An outdoor area set aside for recreation and play, especially one containing equipment such as seesaws and swings. 2.   A field or sphere of unrestricted pleasurable activity:  "Foreign affairs had been T.R.'s personal playground during his Presidency"   (John Dos Passos). 1.  an outdoor area for children's play, esp one having swings, slides, etc, or adjoining a school 2.  a place or region particularly popular as a sports or holiday resort 3.  a sphere of activity:  reading was his private playground .     1.   an area used by children for outdoor recreation, usu. containing play equipment such as slides and swings.     2.   any popular recreation area, as a resort.     3.   the area or sphere of a particular activity. 